##1.

As a user
So that I can keep track of my tasks
I want to check if a text includes the string #TODO.


##2.

# method: 
check_the_text(text)

# text: 
a string given

# report: 
a variable returning either true or false depending on 
whether the specific tect "TODO" is found in the string

# body of method: 
{string_split = text.split("")}
{if "TODO" found then return true, else return false}


##3. 

check_the_text("This is a TODO list") => true

check_the_text("There is just a list without the checking word") => false

